parcel.description:
ハチ公の寺院 

Temple of the Great Akita Inu Hachikō. 
Remembered for his remarkable loyalty to his owner, Hidesaburō Ueno, for whom he continued to wait for over nine years following Ueno's death.

Built for the $AKITA community, this space is open to all doggo lovers who want to take a moment to stop looking at the charts, breathe in, and breathe out. Eternal gratitude to Foreign Organism for this build-out.
parcel.name: Hachikō no jiin
